The paper proposes a new method for representation learning using variational autoencoders (VAEs) with Bayesian nonparametric priors. The focus is on learning a hierarchical structure of latent semantic concepts underlying the data corpus, which is particularly relevant to machine learning subfields such as natural language processing (NLP), computer vision (CV), and neural networks (NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
